==Class Abilities==

===Hero===
* Unique class - only the main character
* Learns both offensive and healing magic
* Cannot change class
* Highest overall stat potential

===Soldier===
* Highest HP and physical defense
* Equips heavy armor and shields
* No magic capability
* Best front-line fighter

===Fighter===
* High agility and critical hit rate
* Cannot equip heavy armor
* No magic capability
* Excels at dealing damage quickly

===Pilgrim===
* Primary healing magic user
* Medium HP and defense
* Learns support and healing spells
* Essential for party survival

===Wizard===
* Powerful offensive magic
* Very low HP and defense
* Highest MP growth
* Glass cannon damage dealer

===Merchant===
* Bonus gold from battles
* Can appraise items
* Limited magic (some healing)
* Useful for economy

===Goof-off===
* Random battle behavior
* Highest luck growth
* Can become Sage without Book of Satori
* Generally weak until class change

===Sage===
* Advanced class, restricted access
* Learns both Pilgrim and Wizard spells
* Requires Book of Satori (except Goof-off)
* Best magical class overall

==Becoming a Sage==

To change to the Sage class:
# Reach level 20 in any class
# Option A: Bring a Book of Satori to Dharma Temple
# Option B: Be a level 20+ Goof-off (no item needed)

The Book of Satori is found in:
* [[Pyramid]] (single copy)
* Monster drops (rare)

